
Instructions for running the simulation
1. Save the codebase to the local area.
2. Install node.js and npm.
3. In a terminal, cd to /back
4. Run “npm install” to install dependencies (libraries called express and nodemon).
5. Run “npm run game” to allow code reload after editing.
6. Run “npm run start” to just allow access to webpage.
7. Using a browser, go to localhost:5000/canvas.html
8. To access the debug console, press F12 or use the options>developer tools in the browser.
